<TITLE> Taskforce formed on milk powder import </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 7 (bdnews24.com)The commerce ministry has formed a task force to investigate illegal imports of milk powder produced in China. In a press release Tuesday, the ministry said an eight member task fore headed by additional commerce secretary Golam Mostafa has been formed to find out how milk powder produced in China is being imported and marketed without registration. The task force will identify which brands of milk powder are being sold in the local market, and the importers concerned. It will verify if the brands were imported under the test certificates as per import policy. The task force will submit its report with recommendations within the next 15 working days. The contaminant melamine has already been detected in Yashli-1 brand milk powder imported to Bangladesh from China. Dhaka-based private laboratory Plasma Plus after primary tests confirmed the presence of melamine in the brand. bdnews
